<h1>Problem 1236 - 2020 Francophone Mathematical Olympiad, Seniors P1 of 4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be an acute triangle with \(AC>AB\), Let \(DEF\) be the intouch triangle with \(D \in (BC)\), \(E \in (AC)\), \(F \in (AB)\), let \(G\) be the intersection of the perpendicular from \(D\) to \(EF\) with \(AB\) and \(X=(ABC)\cap (AEF)\).</p>
<p>Prove that \(B\), \(D\), \(G\) and \(X\) are concyclic.</p>
